Class ArrayStack<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.stack.adt.ArrayStack<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of all objects to store in the stack
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    StackInterface<T>

    public final class ArrayStack<T>
extends java.lang.Object
implements StackInterface<T>
    A class of stacks whose entries are stored in an array.
    Version:
    4.0, 4.1 2019-02-08 add toArray(), toString() and main(), 4.2 2019-02-09
    • reverse implementation to store bottom of the stack in this.stack[stack.length-1] instead of this.stack[0]
    finish implementation per assignment, 5.1 2019-06-09
    • update to match 5th edition of textbook
    • enhance checkCapacity() per updated requirements
    , 5.2.0 2019-06-30 add size() for enhanced testing, 5.3.0 2020-02-17 cleanup toward DRCo coding standard compliance, 5.4.0 2020-06-03
    • enhancements for testing
    • move testing methods to the end of the class
    • add missing reset/set of integrityOK in ensureCapacity()
    , 5.5.0 2020-10-07
    • switch to enhanced testing infrastructure
    • switch back to StackInterface rather than TestableStackInterface
    • xxx
    Author:
    Frank M. Carrano, Timothy M. Henry, Dave Rosenberg
